d/g3813c.la000444", "http://www.loc.gov/resource/g3813c.la000444/"], "campaigns": [], "contributor": ["neumann, louis e.", "hart, chas. (charles)", "beers, comstock & cline", "beers, f. w. (frederick w.)"], "date": "1872", "dates": ["1872"], "description": ["General-content county map also showing rural buildings and householders' names; city/village insets also show real-property tracts, building outlines, and owners' names. Hand col. to emphasize township boundaries, township territories, and insets. Originally printed on 4 sheets (later conjoined). LC copy imperfect: Torn at fold lines, annotated in margins in lead pencil, sheets halved to enable folding, hemmed at upper/lower edges. Includes \"Table of air-line distances\", business directories, and population table. City and village insets: Cape May City -- Cape May Court House -- Cold Spring -- Green Creek -- South Dennisville -- North Dennisville -- Marshallville -- Sea Shore Road [4 insets] -- Tuckahoe -- Seaville -- Petersburgh -- South Seaville -- Goshen -- South Mayville & Gravelly Run. LC Land ownership maps, 444 Available also through the Library of Congress Web site as a raster image. 2 copies"], "digitized": true, "extract_timestamp": "2026-04-29T15:39:17.610Z", "group": ["gmd.mar", "catalog-split-06", "catalog", "general-maps", "main-catalog-split-06"], "hassegments": false, "id": "http://www.loc.gov/item/2012592359/", "image_url": ["https://tile.loc.gov/storage-services/service/gmd/gmd381/g3813/g3813c/la000444.gif", "https://tile.loc.gov/storage-services/service/gmd/gmd381/g3813/g3813c/la000444.gif#h=168&w=150", "https://tile.loc.gov/image-services/iiif/service:gmd:gmd381:g3813:g3813c:la000444/full/pct:12.5/0/default.jpg#h=2050&w=1832", "https://tile.loc.gov/image-services/iiif/service:gmd:gmd381:g3813:g3813c:la000444/full/pct:25/0/default.jpg#h=4101&w=3664"], "index": 1, "language": ["english"], "location": ["new jersey", "cape may", "cape may county", "cape may court house", "united states"], "mim